reviews.text: The food here is excellent! A lot of very diverse options with lots of variety for all tastes. The prices are great! I had three custom tacos that were a decent size and spent less than $10. I'm from Phoenix, AZ and I highly recommend this place!

This is my favorite taco place in the Cleveland area. Love taking people from out of town here. The food is all really good and they always have awesome unique drinks on the menu. The different shells for the tacos really make this place unique. Can't wait to come back.

Amazing service!  We brought six kids and four adults here for lunch and the staff was incredible. We were blown away by the friendliness and attention given to us to make our lunch so awesome. The food was delicious as always and came out very quickly. The chips were constantly refilled which kept the kids very happy. The french toast was delicious!  The only tricky part was parking. We used the valet service from the hotel next door because street parking was restricted. The hefty valet fee was more than worth it though because we had such a great experience. Thank you, Barrio!!

Serve and food was awesome! The Cher concert let out, and the place was instantly flooded. The staff was amazing. Service wasn't interrupted at all. They sailed through the challenge with ease. Food was spot on. I would definitely go back. Loved their flavors. Perfect pricing.

I love the ambience. The way the natural light hits during the day makes it bright. Such a great place to catch up with friends. Everything on the menu is delicious. Worth it all. 5 stars.Worth giving it a try! Definitely coming back!

So I had my order delivered to West Duluth. My delivery driver was very prompt, even though he forgot my soda at the store, he went and grabbed some at the nearest convenient store. Now that is service! I have never had a bad experience with Pizza Luce, but this last experience will definitely make me order more often from them! Kudos to their delivery drivers.

We ordered in, it got to us in the time they said it would , but our pizza seemed old , half cold and taste wasn't even close to amazing. same with our cheesy bread, not impressed.. the only thing we ate the most of was the wings. For how expensive it was I thought it was going to be amazing, it was not. I definitely will not eat here again. Again, I am not impressed with the experience 🤦

I was in town for a work meeting and the whole team went here for lunch. For a large group and a busy lunch schedule they still got our food to us quickly. The food was worth the visit and the ambiance was awesome.

One of my favorite restaurants in Duluth. We could not decide on which pizza to order so the server suggested that we get 2 different kinds on 1 pizza. It was perfect for us and the food was delicious as usual.
So many great vegetarian, vegan, dairy and gluten free options! Gluten free stuffed shells were amazing. Molly bar was very good. Great and quick service and very reasonable prices.

Due to a mix up on my part with my landlord my water was shut off yesterday due to the land lord ending service. As a pet owner with two large dogs and a cat as well as a roommate I needed the water back on quickly. I went in, signed up and explained the situation and within 3 hours my water was back on. I realize this is definitely not the norm as far as turnaround time and truly appreciate the extra mile these folks went to help me.

While I do understand that sometimes water outages happen, my whole neighborhood has been without water over 17 hours (and counting!) with no explanation and no update as to how long it would take to fix.  There was no natural disaster or major reason why our water should be out this long.  Living without water in your house is a major deal and some update should be given to customers.  I asked to speak to the manager after I got no update from the customer service rep, but she said that because I wasn't the primary account holder (I rent), I wasn't able to.  So that's why I'm leaving a review.  Aqua Texas, you really need to change your policies and better serve your customers.

I had three of their pipes deteriorate and leak in my backyard. I had to spend several hours waiting for the contractors they hired to come and repair the pipes all three times and they left my yard lob sided from the dirt they didn't level.

I called Aqua regarding a water leak on their main, near my neighbors house. I first noticed the leak almost four months ago. I finally caught the neighbor at home about two months ago and they said it had been reported. Aqua sent someone out to paint a blue mark indicating where the leak is at. This leak is still ongoing, possibly contaminating the community water supply. The response from the Aqua emergency phone number was "Sir, you'll have to call back Monday after 9:00". Called back only to hear them say there was no report of a leak at the address, and there was no such address on Lakeridge  Loop. Tried to help this neighbor, but sorry, they're on their own now. It may get fixed after a meter reader falls through a sink hole caused by the leak.
If I could give them zero stars, I would. I was on hold for a supervisor for over 20 minutes and still never spoke to one. Worst customer service!

So, yesterday, after enjoying our Free Ice Cream Cone at Ben & Jerry's, me and my friends headed over to the Hard Times Cafe for dinner.  Now, we had eaten there before, a long time ago, and we were looking forward to our meal.  First off, the staff was friendly and welcoming.  The waiter asked, right off the bat, if we wanted separate checks - which was nice because we did.  The cafe wasn't too busy, it was a little after 7 PM, so there was no waiting.
I had the 5-way Chili Mac with Veggie Chili and a Diet Coke.  They started us out with corn bread after serving us our drinks and our food was served pretty quickly and was tasty.  Afterwards, even though I shouldn't have, I ordered a Reese's Peanut Butter Pie.  To be honest I was full but the dessert menu looked so good!  And the pie was perfect - with whipped cream and some chocolate syrup. 
Overall the price wasn't that bad either, even including the tip.  I have to say the Hard Times Cafe is one of those places where you CAN visit it a few times a season without worrying about your wallet and just enjoy the food.  Also, it is far enough away from the Waterfront NOT to be too crowded or filled with tourists.  But it also means it is close to the King Street Station when you need to get back home via one of the buses or the subway.  As we all had to get home via public transport it was nice that we were served so quickly and were so close to the station.  Yet, we never felt rushed!  I wish I could give them more stars - I have been to a few Hard Times Cafe and have NEVER been disappointed.

This is a pretty simple little place. It's a chain, or it used to be. Most or all of the other locations have closed. They serve Tex-Mex bar food, mainly chili. They have four kinds of chili, including vegetarian. They also serve Shiner Bock beer from Texas. The servers are all very nice and helpful. Good for a quick bite or a relaxing beer. The chili, cheese and spaghetti 3-way is filling, but could do with a little less spaghetti and more chili and cheese.

Great flavors of chili. Texas, Cincinnati, red Texas, and vegetarian. We loved them all. The homemade cornbread was delicious. The only thing I would have liked better were the beans to be cooked longer. They were too hard when biting into them. I had the five-way chili. Absolute delicacy!

I understand that it has been around for quite some time but the place just feels dark and dirty and not in a cool dive bar kind of way.  Had their chili (Texas style not their signature one) it was ok.  Not unhappy but not excited about going back either
This place has truly awesome chili choices! They also serve a bowl of water tots with chili, cheese, and sour cream... Oh my gosh, so good!

Decent amount of choices on the menu. Taste buds did not get tickled, nothing to write home about. The mushroom mutter was ordinary; butter chicken was alright, may be the chicken was a tad under cooked (I like mine well done), but tasty. Service was good.

Can improve on multiple fronts if they want, or not, given there aren't as many Indian food choices around here.

Great food, but the service was stellar. I am Indian and have travelled to Nepal. All the staff is Nepali, and the flavors are completely authentic. The memos, dumplings, have  a delightful curried filling that has just a touch of heat. It's just the start of a meal with great but not overwhelming flavor.
Outstanding Indian food. Fair prices, especially in a tourist driven location. Delivery makes this one a great option when staying in the area as well.
Always great meals! Some of the best Nepalese/Indian food in Southern California. Love this place!
Decent place for Indian food at Big bear. Momos (dumplings) are must try. Located on a beautiful street to walk and shop.

I LOVE this place! The food is to die for and the atmosphere is so warm and friendly.

Always a fantastic meal every time we go. Highly recommended. I'd say one if the best restaurants in Derby.
Yes! Amazing restaurant! Waiters are super friendly and the food is really delicious. Took my son down and we both really enjoyed nice and authentic decor and food 5 stars fully deserved 👍

Booked a table for my partner's birthday and had the most excellent dining experience. The food was excellent and the service matches and food quality. Excellent attention to detail and caring attentive service.

Would absolutely recommend especially to those experiencing the loss of MexiCo from the Intu centre. (I was), this is way better!

Parking is easy behind the building (free after 8pm) and you will leave full and satisfied!

Ordered from them for the first time, and my goodness you couldn't be more AMAZING! Genuinely the best burrito I have ever had in my LIFE! Incredible, so flavourful, an amazing price and comes with fries?
Pepitos is amazing, please go here and get a burrito! You will not be disappointed.
11/10.
Really nice atmosphere, delicious food. Highly recommended!

Had a family birthday gathering here. The staff was amazing catering to our many needs. We were a group of about 30 ages from 0-70+. Fantastic service and fabulous meal. Highly recommended  by  all of us.

I visited tony romas for a steak. The meal was very good and so was the service. The manager introduced himself to the customers welcoming everyone I thought was very nice of him. I highly recommend this restaurant for a high quality meal and for socializing it has a good relaxing quiet atmosphere. I will be returning again very soon.
Had the lunch burger, it was pretty good. Service was good, staff were friendly. I noticed that the lunch menu increased in price - that was a bummer. $13 for a burger?! highway robbery! ;-)

Lethbridge's best statehouse! In a landscape of top price Dinning, you can't get better then Toni Roma's. The food is all great. The portions are very good. Whenever we can, about once in two or three months, my wife and myself splurge and go to Tony Roma's.

Oh... WOW. Great service. LOVE the hostess, Brenna. Excellent costumer service and politeness from her. And the server, PARIS! Outstanding service, best waitress we’ve ever had. The manager, Kacie, was very kind and very welcoming. The food was just amazing. The atmosphere of the restaurant was very warming. Will definitely be visiting again :)

I went with a friend on a Wednesday evening for dinner. The place was busy but there was a table available. We had the cutlet which came with a thick meatball soup. The dish had vegetables and potatoes with plenty of tasty gravy. The food was like home made by mom. The food was excellent and the service was good considering the fact that it was busy. We had a German beer each. The total bill was about $80. The place is nice and casual and close to parking. I would recommend this place and would go again.

Go about 6 times a year. Good food, uniforms are dated but it's a theme thing. Soups are always tremendous. We ate here last night - group of 4. We waited over an hour for a table, but it was so worth it! The schnitzel was cooked to perfection, and the potato soup was delish! Our waitress was very efficient! It is definitely worth the drive from Burlington - it’s one of our favourites! Still as good as ever! Will return soon!!!

The place has an unique interior. Service was friendly and helpful, food was typical German food, schnitzel and sausages etc. The schnitzel was huge, enough to feed 2 people. The side portions were also generous. You will not leave hungry. Beer was good.

This is my first minor complaint. Got there shortly after 6 got seated right-a-way. But waited over a hour for dinner to be brought to our table. Waitress said they had a birthday party of 20 in the room. (As per Jenny)
Been there a couple time and waited for a table for good half hour and out the door in another 30 to 45 minutes less than 2 then tonight's visit.
Yes will still go because of the food.
New menus but same decor. Even with new owners, food still great. Got rid of my favourite menu item, but lots of choices left. If you're vegan, don't bother coming here.
